  "text": "Exercise has been associated with reductions in fatigue and depression, and improvements in mobility and QOL. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] There are additional benefits including improvements in cardiorespiratory capacity, muscle strength and endurance, and balance. [CITATION_4] Such evidence was reviewed in a consensus meeting, titled Exercise as a Prescriptive Therapy in Multiple Sclerosis, wherein there was a strong statement for exercise as one of the best therapies available for inclusion in the comprehensive care.",
